In [[1475 DR]], Chant was given a [[magic]] [[scarf]] to hold by the [[Deva (aasimar)|deva]] [[Demascus]]. Demascus retrieved the scarf in [[1479 DR]] and Chant helped Demascus track down and destroy a [[rakshasa]] who was behind demonic cult activity in [[Akan没l]].	

In [[Marpenoth|Leafall]] of 1479 DR, Queen [[Arathane]] asked Demascus and Riltana to investigate potential trouble at an [[arambarium]] mine on [[Ithimir Isle]] off the coast of Akan没l.{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|518}}  While investigating a warehouse owned by Raneger, the two stumbled opon a plot by [[drow]] from [[Menzoberranzan]] to steal Akan没l's supply of arambarium ore.{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|720}}

Because of Chant's ties to Raneger, Demascus asked Chant to make introductions to the crime lord.  Raneger agreed to work with Demascus and Chant and allowed Chant's son [[Jaul Morven|Jaul]], who was an employee of Raneger's, to travel with the heroes.  Chant and friends foiled the drow plot and returned the aramabarium to Queen Arathane.{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|3592}}
